	(167, 1, 'Botble\\ACL\\Models\\User', 'post', '{"name":"Does AI Owe You? (Axios AM)","model":"Botble\\\\Blog\\\\Models\\\\Post","slug":"exploring-the-benefits-of-mysql-for-large-scale-projects","slug_id":"25","is_slug_editable":"1","description":"A deep dive into whether individuals should be compensated when their online content\\u2014social posts, blogs, other digital contributions\\u2014is used without consent to train AI models.","is_featured":"0","content":"<p style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;overflow-wrap:break-word;padding:0px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">You could easily<\\/strong> live without AI. But AI wouldn\'t exist without you, <em style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\"><i>Jim VandeHei and Mike Allen write in a \\"Behind the Curtain\\" column.<\\/i><\\/em><\\/p><ul style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;list-style:url(&quot;https:\\/\\/static.axios.com\\/img\\/axios-site\\/bullet-filled.svg&quot;) none;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;padding:0px 0px 0px 18px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\\"><li style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">So does AI owe you<\\/strong> for your small part in creating it?<\\/li><\\/ul><p style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;overflow-wrap:break-word;padding:0px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">Why it matters: <\\/strong>This question sits at the very heart of legal, economic, moral and societal debates unfolding before us today \\u2014 and deep into the future. The answer will unlock everything from court verdicts to the fortunes of financial winners and losers years from now.<\\/p><p style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;overflow-wrap:break-word;padding:0px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\\">\\ud83d\\uddbc\\ufe0f <strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">The big picture:<\\/strong> First, the facts. Large language models (LLMs) such as OpenAI\'s ChatGPT or Anthropic\'s Claude were built by ingesting the totality of human information online \\u2014 everything from news stories by Axios to social media postings by you.<\\/p><ul style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;list-style:url(&quot;https:\\/\\/static.axios.com\\/img\\/axios-site\\/bullet-filled.svg&quot;) none;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;padding:0px 0px 0px 18px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\\"><li style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:12px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">AI developers call<\\/strong> this \\"training data\\" because they used the internet \\u2014 and all its content \\u2014 to train machines to think, reason and operate like the humans feeding the web.&nbsp;The goal: think better, faster and cheaper than us. Then, unleash these machines everywhere for everything.<\\/li><li style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">By 2025,<\\/strong> content produced by billions of internet users helped shape the massive digital corpus that modern AI models were trained on \\u2014 mostly through public, web-accessible data. Think any content \\u2014 posts, blogs, forums, websites, Wikipedia edits, reviews, and videos.<\\/li><\\/ul><p style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;overflow-wrap:break-word;padding:0px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">Some content owners<\\/strong> \\u2014 mass producers and individual creators \\u2014 are suing AI companies for using their content without permission. The litigation \\u2014 by media companies, music producers, book publishers \\u2014 is often brought under copyright laws. AI makers defend their use of protected content by invoking long-contested \\"fair use\\" principles.<\\/p><ul style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;list-style:url(&quot;https:\\/\\/static.axios.com\\/img\\/axios-site\\/bullet-filled.svg&quot;) none;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;padding:0px 0px 0px 18px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:ini