link-text=\\"Axios\\" data-vars-click-url=\\"https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/partnering-with-axios-expands-openai-work-with-the-news-industry\\/\\" data-vars-item=\\"in_content_link\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Axios<\\/a>, have struck deals with OpenAI for use of their content.<\\/li><\\/ul><p style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;overflow-wrap:break-word;padding:0px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">The Supreme Court could<\\/strong> ultimately decide \\u2014 likely years from now \\u2014 whether the owners of these LLMs violated federal law with their training tactics.<\\/p><ul style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;list-style:url(&quot;https:\\/\\/static.axios.com\\/img\\/axios-site\\/bullet-filled.svg&quot;) none;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;padding:0px 0px 0px 18px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\\"><li style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">\\"We\'re at the top<\\/strong> of the first inning of understanding how the courts are going to define fair use as it applies to AI training,\\" <a class=\\"gtmContentClick\\" style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(34, 87, 218);font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;text-decoration-color:inherit;text-decoration-line:underline;text-decoration-style:inherit;text-decoration-thickness:inherit;\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/copyrightalliance.org\\/about\\/keith-kupferschmid\\/\\" data-vars-link-text=\\"Keith Kupferschmid\\" data-vars-click-url=\\"https:\\/\\/copyrightalliance.org\\/about\\/keith-kupferschmid\\/\\" data-vars-item=\\"in_content_link\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Keith Kupferschmid<\\/a>, president and CEO of the Copyright Alliance, tells us. He said cases involving images and music will be more difficult for AI companies to win, while cases involving text are more complex.<\\/li><\\/ul><p style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;overflow-wrap:break-word;padding:0px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">But what about <\\/strong><em style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\"><i><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">you?<\\/strong><\\/i><\\/em><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\"> <\\/strong>If you ever posted a comment on Reddit, or tweeted, or shared pictures on Instagram, or posted a rant on Facebook, you\'re a tiny part of the LLMs\' brains.<\\/p><ul style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;list-style:url(&quot;https:\\/\\/static.axios.com\\/img\\/axios-site\\/bullet-filled.svg&quot;) none;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;padding:0px 0px 0px 18px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\\"><li style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">Your words were<\\/strong> gobbled up to help train the machines, creating untold riches for tech companies and investors. But no one asked your permission or offered to compensate for that tiny part you played in making others rich.<\\/li><\\/ul><p style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;overflow-wrap:break-word;padding:0px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">It\'s doubtful<\\/strong> you\'ll get a penny for your time or mind now. President Trump, in his speech at last month\'s <a class=\\"gtmContentClick\\" style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(34, 87, 218);font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;text-decoration-color:inherit;text-decoration-line:underline;text-decoration-style:inherit;text-decoration-thickness:inherit;\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=tBNX9x5GgPE\\" data-vars-link-text=\\"AI summit\\" data-vars-click-url=\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=tBNX9x5GgPE\\" data-vars-item=\\"in_content_link\\" target=\\"_blank\\">AI summit<\\/a> in Washington, made plain his opposition to companies doling out cash based on derivative use of the internet (unless it\'s blatant piracy).<\\/p><ul style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;list-style:url(&quot;https:\\/\\/static.axios.com\\/img\\/axios-site\\/bullet-filled.svg&quot;) none;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;padding:0px 0px 0px 18px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\\"><li style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:12px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">\\"[W]hen you read<\\/strong> something and when it goes into this vast intelligence <em style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\"><i>machine, <\\/i><\\/em>we\'ll call it, you cannot expect to every time, every single time, say: \'Oh, let\'s pay this one that much,\'\\" <a class=\\"gtmContentClick\\" style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(34, 87, 218);font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;text-decoration-color:inherit;text-decoration-line:underline;text-decoration-style:inherit;text-decoration-thickness:inherit;\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.techpolicy.press\\/transcript-donald-trumps-address-at-winning-the-ai-race-event\\/\\" data-vars-link-text=\\"he said\\" data-vars-click-url=\\"https:\\/\\/www.techpolicy.press\\/transcript-donald-trumps-address-at-winning-the-ai-race-event\\/\\" data-vars-item=\\"in_content_link\\" target=\\"_blank\\">he said<\\/a>. \\"[W]e have to allow AI to use that pool of knowledge without going through the complexity of contract negotiations, of which there would be <em style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\"><i>thousands<\\/i><\\/em> for every time we use AI.\\"<\\/li><li style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">His main point:<\\/strong> It would give China an insurmountable edge if we tie ourselves in knots over who owes what to whom.<\\/li><\\/ul><p style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;overflow-wrap:break-word;padding:0px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">But some AI leaders, <\\/strong>most notably Anthropic\'s Dario Amodei, <a class=\\"gtmContentClick\\" style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(34, 87, 218);font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;text-decoration-color:inherit;text-decoration-line:underline;text-decoration-style:inherit;text-decoration-thickness:inherit;\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.axios.com\\/2025\\/05\\/28\\/ai-jobs-white-collar-unemployment-anthropic\\" data-vars-link-text=\\"argue you should benefit\\" data-vars-click-url=\\"https:\\/\\/www.axios.com\\/2025\\/05\\/28\\/ai-jobs-white-collar-unemployment-anthropic\\" data-vars-item=\\"in_content_link\\" target=\\"_self\\">argue you should benefit<\\/a> \\u2014 in the future. They believe if AI only enriches the big companies and investors, America will face a rebellion \\u2014 and potentially sky-high unemployment.<\\/p><ul style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;list-style:url(&quot;https:\\/\\/static.axios.com\\/img\\/axios-site\\/bullet-filled.svg&quot;) none;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;padding:0px 0px 0px 18px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\\"><li style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:12px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">So instead of <\\/strong>paying you now, which might hamstring the companies, they talk of spreading the wealth if AI truly creates trillions of dollars of wealth long-term. This could be as novel as a guaranteed minimum income (universal basic income, or UBI), funded by AI companies, or as ordinary as higher taxes on AI to fund social programs and government overall.<\\/li><li style=\\"border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">Or it could be<\\/strong> a private sector indirect benefit of higher growth, driving higher wages.<\\/li><\\/ul><p style=\\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(51, 51, 53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;margin-block:24px;margin:0px;orphans:2;overflow-wrap:break-word;padding:0px;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"--tw-font-weight:600;border-style:solid;border-width:0px;box-sizing:border-box;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">Regardless,<\\/strong> the AI companies will get a lot bigger and a lot richer \\u2014 before you get a penny, if you ever do.<\\/p><p>&nbsp;<\\/p>","gallery":null,"seo_meta":{"seo_title":null,"seo_description":null,"index":"index"},"seo_meta_image":null,"status":"published","categories":["4"],"image":"main\\/posts\\/7.png","tag":"[{\\"value\\":\\"Vietnam Developer\\"}]","allow_comments":"0","submitter":"apply"}', 'updated', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/138.0.0.0 Safari/537.36', '127.0.0.1', 1, 'Botble\\ACL\\Models\\User', 8, 'Does AI Owe You? (Axios AM)', 'primary', '2025-08-07 03:39:54', '2025-08-07 03:39:54'),
	(168, 1, 'Botble\\ACL\\Models\\User', 'post', '{"name":"Does AI Owe You? (Axios AM)","model":"Botble\\\\Blog\\\\Models\\\\Post","slug":"exploring-the-benefits-of-mysql-for-large-scale-projects","slug_id":"25","is_slug_editable":"1","description":"A deep dive into whether individuals should be compensated when their online content\\u2014social posts, blogs, other digital contributions\\u2014is used without consent to train AI models.","is_featured":"0","content":"<p style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;margin:0px;padding:0px;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">You could easily<\\/strong> live without AI. But AI wouldn\'t exist without you, <em style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\"><i>Jim VandeHei and Mike Allen write in a \\"Behind the Curtain\\" column.<\\/i><\\/em><\\/p><ul style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;list-style:none url(&quot;https:\\/\\/static.axios.com\\/img\\/axios-site\\/bullet-filled.svg&quot;);margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 18px;word-spacing:0px;\\"><li style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">So does AI owe you<\\/strong> for your small part in creating it?<\\/li><\\/ul><p style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;margin:0px;padding:0px;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">Why it matters: <\\/strong>This question sits at the very heart of legal, economic, moral and societal debates unfolding before us today \\u2014 and deep into the future. The answer will unlock everything from court verdicts to the fortunes of financial winners and losers years from now.<\\/p><p style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;margin:0px;padding:0px;word-spacing:0px;\\">\\ud83d\\uddbc\\ufe0f <strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">The big picture:<\\/strong> First, the facts. Large language models (LLMs) such as OpenAI\'s ChatGPT or Anthropic\'s Claude were built by ingesting the totality of human information online \\u2014 everything from news stories by Axios to social media postings by you.<\\/p><ul style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;list-style:none url(&quot;https:\\/\\/static.axios.com\\/img\\/axios-site\\/bullet-filled.svg&quot;);margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 18px;word-spacing:0px;\\"><li style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:12px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">AI developers call<\\/strong> this \\"training data\\" because they used the internet \\u2014 and all its content \\u2014 to train machines to think, reason and operate like the humans feeding the web.&nbsp;The goal: think better, faster and cheaper than us. Then, unleash these machines everywhere for everything.<\\/li><li style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">By 2025,<\\/strong> content produced by billions of internet users helped shape the massive digital corpus that modern AI models were trained on \\u2014 mostly through public, web-accessible data. Think any content \\u2014 posts, blogs, forums, websites, Wikipedia edits, reviews, and videos.<\\/li><\\/ul><p style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;margin:0px;padding:0px;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">Some content owners<\\/strong> \\u2014 mass producers and individual creators \\u2014 are suing AI companies for using their content without permission. The litigation \\u2014 by media companies, music producers, book publishers \\u2014 is often brought under copyright laws. AI makers defend their use of protected content by invoking long-contested \\"fair use\\" principles.<\\/p><ul style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;list-style:none url(&quot;https:\\/\\/static.axios.com\\/img\\/axios-site\\/bullet-filled.svg&quot;);margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 18px;word-spacing:0px;\\"><li style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:12px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">Copyright owners<\\/strong> have filed close to 50 lawsuits against AI companies in federal court, according to the <a class=\\"gtmContentClick\\" style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(34,87,218);font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/copyrightalliance.org\\/ai-copyright-infringement-cases-insights\\/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noreferrer noopener\\">Copyright Alliance<\\/a>, which <a class=\\"gtmContentClick\\" style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(34,87,218);font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/copyrightalliance.org\\/about\\/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noreferrer noopener\\">represents creators<\\/a>.<\\/li><li style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><a class=\\"gtmContentClick\\" style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(34,87,218);font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/copyrightalliance.org\\/artificial-intelligence-copyright\\/licensing\\/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noreferrer noopener\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">Some publishers<\\/strong><\\/a><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">,<\\/strong> including <a class=\\"gtmContentClick\\" style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(34,87,218);font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/investors.newscorp.com\\/news-releases\\/news-release-details\\/news-corp-and-openai-sign-landmark-multi-year-global-partnership\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noreferrer noopener\\">News Corp<\\/a> and <a class=\\"gtmContentClick\\" style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(34,87,218);font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/openai.com\\/index\\/partnering-with-axios-expands-openai-work-with-the-news-industry\\/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noreferrer noopener\\">Axios<\\/a>, have struck deals with OpenAI for use of their content.<\\/li><\\/ul><p style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;margin:0px;padding:0px;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">The Supreme Court could<\\/strong> ultimately decide \\u2014 likely years from now \\u2014 whether the owners of these LLMs violated federal law with their training tactics.<\\/p><ul style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;list-style:none url(&quot;https:\\/\\/static.axios.com\\/img\\/axios-site\\/bullet-filled.svg&quot;);margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 18px;word-spacing:0px;\\"><li style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">\\"We\'re at the top<\\/strong> of the first inning of understanding how the courts are going to define fair use as it applies to AI training,\\" <a class=\\"gtmContentClick\\" style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(34,87,218);font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/copyrightalliance.org\\/about\\/keith-kupferschmid\\/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noreferrer noopener\\">Keith Kupferschmid<\\/a>, president and CEO of the Copyright Alliance, tells us. He said cases involving images and music will be more difficult for AI companies to win, while cases involving text are more complex.<\\/li><\\/ul><p style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;margin:0px;padding:0px;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">But what about <\\/strong><em style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\"><i><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">you?<\\/strong><\\/i><\\/em><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\"> <\\/strong>If you ever posted a comment on Reddit, or tweeted, or shared pictures on Instagram, or posted a rant on Facebook, you\'re a tiny part of the LLMs\' brains.<\\/p><ul style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;list-style:none url(&quot;https:\\/\\/static.axios.com\\/img\\/axios-site\\/bullet-filled.svg&quot;);margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 18px;word-spacing:0px;\\"><li style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">Your words were<\\/strong> gobbled up to help train the machines, creating untold riches for tech companies and investors. But no one asked your permission or offered to compensate for that tiny part you played in making others rich.<\\/li><\\/ul><p style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;margin:0px;padding:0px;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">It\'s doubtful<\\/strong> you\'ll get a penny for your time or mind now. President Trump, in his speech at last month\'s <a class=\\"gtmContentClick\\" style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(34,87,218);font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=tBNX9x5GgPE\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noreferrer noopener\\">AI summit<\\/a> in Washington, made plain his opposition to companies doling out cash based on derivative use of the internet (unless it\'s blatant piracy).<\\/p><ul style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;list-style:none url(&quot;https:\\/\\/static.axios.com\\/img\\/axios-site\\/bullet-filled.svg&quot;);margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 18px;word-spacing:0px;\\"><li style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:12px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">\\"[W]hen you read<\\/strong> something and when it goes into this vast intelligence <em style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\"><i>machine, <\\/i><\\/em>we\'ll call it, you cannot expect to every time, every single time, say: \'Oh, let\'s pay this one that much,\'\\" <a class=\\"gtmContentClick\\" style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(34,87,218);font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.techpolicy.press\\/transcript-donald-trumps-address-at-winning-the-ai-race-event\\/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" rel=\\"noreferrer noopener\\">he said<\\/a>. \\"[W]e have to allow AI to use that pool of knowledge without going through the complexity of contract negotiations, of which there would be <em style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\"><i>thousands<\\/i><\\/em> for every time we use AI.\\"<\\/li><li style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">His main point:<\\/strong> It would give China an insurmountable edge if we tie ourselves in knots over who owes what to whom.<\\/li><\\/ul><p style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;margin:0px;padding:0px;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">But some AI leaders, <\\/strong>most notably Anthropic\'s Dario Amodei, <a class=\\"gtmContentClick\\" style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(34,87,218);font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\" href=\\"https:\\/\\/www.axios.com\\/2025\\/05\\/28\\/ai-jobs-white-collar-unemployment-anthropic\\">argue you should benefit<\\/a> \\u2014 in the future. They believe if AI only enriches the big companies and investors, America will face a rebellion \\u2014 and potentially sky-high unemployment.<\\/p><ul style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;list-style:none url(&quot;https:\\/\\/static.axios.com\\/img\\/axios-site\\/bullet-filled.svg&quot;);margin:0px;padding:0px 0px 0px 18px;word-spacing:0px;\\"><li style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:12px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">So instead of <\\/strong>paying you now, which might hamstring the companies, they talk of spreading the wealth if AI truly creates trillions of dollars of wealth long-term. This could be as novel as a guaranteed minimum income (universal basic income, or UBI), funded by AI companies, or as ordinary as higher taxes on AI to fund social programs and government overall.<\\/li><li style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin-bottom:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-top:24px;padding:0px 0px 0px 8px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">Or it could be<\\/strong> a private sector indirect benefit of higher growth, driving higher wages.<\\/li><\\/ul><p style=\\"border-style:solid;color:rgb(51,51,53);font-family:Atiza, serif;font-size:18px;font-style:normal;font-weight:400;margin:0px;padding:0px;word-spacing:0px;\\"><strong style=\\"border-style:solid;font-family:Atiza, serif;margin:0px;padding:0px;\\">Regardless,<\\/strong> the AI companies will get a lot bigger and a lot richer \\u2014 before you get a penny, if you ever do.<\\/p><p>&nbsp;<\\/p>","gallery":null,"seo_meta":{"seo_title":null,"seo_description":null,"index":"index"},"seo_meta_image":null,"status":"published","categories":["4"],"image":"main\\/posts\\/7.png","tag":"[{\\"value\\":\\"Vietnam Developer\\"}]","allow_comments":"0"}', 'updated', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/138.0.0.0 Safari/537.36', '127.0.0.1', 1, 'Botble\\ACL\\Models\\User', 8, 'Does AI Owe You? (Axios AM)', 'primary', '2025-08-07 03:40:56', '2025-08-07 03:40:56'),
